content.description: This is the right of two bolted face climbs on a featured face on the western part of the Solomon Islands. 3 bolts lead to a 2 bolt anchor.
content.location: The Solomon Islands are the southern most clump of climbable rock off of Geotour Rd.

climbs.name: Buttress Buttress Golly
climbs.fa: Todd Gordon, George Armstrong, Greg Epperson

content.description: This 2 pitch route ascend the north face of a formation on the north section of the Solomon Islands.  The first pitch goes up cracks to a ledge. The 2nd pitch goes the face past bolts into a wide crack which leads to the summit.
content.protection: A trad rack plus quick draws for the bolted face section.  Larger cams for the wide section at the top.
content.location: Northern most section of the Solomon Islands.  The Solomon Islands are the southern most climbing rock off of Geotour Rd.

content.description: This excellent route is the left of two routes on the south face of a featured face on the western part of the Solomon Islands. 3 bolts lead to a 2 bolt anchor.
content.location: This is the southern most group climbable rock off of Geotour Road.

content.description: This route is located just left and around the corner from Bury the Pickle/Eat Me Volumne 23. The Black Eel is on the west face. 3 bolts lead to a 2 bolt anchor.
content.location: This climb is located on the west face of a feature face on the western most section of the Solomon Island.  The Solomon Islands are the soutern most clump of climbable rock off of Geotour Rd.
